{"questionId":"22756","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Juri skis from the top of a hill to a finishing point at the bottom of the hill. She takes the&nbsp;shortest route, heading directly to the finishing point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mtext>F</mtext><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/b545a0c7374880c387bb91f730e082e49cd1d965.png\"></p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> define the height of the hill above <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>F</mtext></math> at a horizontal distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> from the starting point&nbsp;at the top of the hill.</p>\n<p>The graph of the <strong>derivative</strong> of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is shown below. The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> has local minima and&nbsp;maxima when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> is equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>e</mi></math>. The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> intersects the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> is&nbsp;equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/b14715e240cbebfa9590e6bf8cef1160b64c19a6.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Interpret this point in the given context.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>the hill is at its steepest / largest slope of hill&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22756","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.8a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Interpret this point in the given context.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.1—Introduction of differential calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.13—Kinematic problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}